%% Activity Diagram - Ticket Sale Flow (Secretary)
%% Updated: 2026-03-10

flowchart TD
    A([Start]) --> B[Secretary opens Trip Detail page]
    B --> C[View seat map with real-time status]
    C --> D{Select available seat/s}

    D --> E{Action type?}
    E -- "Sell (V key)" --> F[Open Ticket Sale Modal]
    E -- "Reserve (R key)" --> G[Open Reservation Modal]

    F --> H{Client registered?}
    G --> H

    H -- Yes --> I[Search and select existing client]
    H -- No --> J[Register new client inline]
    J --> I

    I --> K{Sale or Reservation?}
    K -- Sale --> L[Select payment method\ncash / QR]
    K -- Reservation --> M[Confirm reservation]

    L --> N[Create ticket\nstate = confirmed]
    M --> O[Create ticket\nstate = pending]

    N --> P[Seat locked via WebSocket\nupdated in real-time]
    O --> P

    P --> Q[Show success notification]
    Q --> R[Seat map refreshes]
    R --> S([End])

    %% Reservation confirmation flow
    subgraph ReservationConfirm ["Later: Confirm Reserved Ticket"]
        R1[Secretary views reserved seat] --> R2[Right-click > Confirm Sale]
        R2 --> R3[Confirm Sale Modal\nshows price]
        R3 --> R4[PUT /tickets/:id\nstate → confirmed]
        R4 --> R5[Seat map refreshes]
    end

    %% Seat change flow
    subgraph SeatChange ["Seat Change Flow"]
        SC1[Right-click occupied seat] --> SC2[Select 'Change Seat']
        SC2 --> SC3[Enter Seat Change Mode\nbanner shown]
        SC3 --> SC4[Click new available seat]
        SC4 --> SC5[Confirm Seat Change Modal]
        SC5 --> SC6[PUT /tickets/:id/change-seat]
    end
